Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
modifyPipelineNetGroup(25.10)                    modifyPipelineNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       modifyPipelineNetGroup  - Modifies the existing net group attributes or
       converts an existing net group added during floorplanning to be of type
       pipeline

Syntax
       modifyPipelineNetGroup

       netGroupName

       [{-inst <instNameListOrRegularExp> |

             -startTerm <termList> -endTerm <termList> |

             -net <listOfNetnamesOrRegularExp> }]

       [-startReserve <distInMicrons>] [-endReserve <distInMicrons>]

       Modifies the existing net group attributes or converts an existing  net
       group  added  during floorplanning to be of type pipeline. This command
       can be used if there are existing pipe line net groups in the design.

Parameters
       -endReserve <ReserveDistanceInMicrons>
              Specifies a distance value from the end points on block boundary
              to the internal connection inside the block  that  needs  to  be
              added  to  the last stage distance, to achieve equidistant spac-
              ing. The unit is in micron.

       -inst <instNameListOrRegularExp>
              Modifies net group to add all nets connected to  the  given  in-
              stances.  The  instances  must all be flip-flops or latches. All
              the nets attached to the D and Q pins are put into the  PFF  net
              group.

       -net <listOfNetNamesOrRegularExp>
              Creates net group of all given nets.

       -startReserve <ReserveDistanceInMicrons>
              Specifies  a  distance  budget  from internal connections inside
              block to the start point of the PFF net. This value is added  to
              the  first  stage  distance when calculating equidistant spacing
              for each stage. The unit is in micron.

       -startTerm <termList>
              Modifies net group to add all data nets between  the  given  end
              points.  The  PFF-chain  is traced from the startTerm, through D
              and Q terminals of PFF(s) until an endTerm is matched.

       -endTerm <termList>
              Modifies net group to add all data nets between  the  given  end
              points.  The  PFF-chain  is traced from the startTerm, through D
              and Q terminals of PFF(s) until an endTerm is matched.

       netGroupName
              Specifies the name of net group.

Example
       The following command modifies the existing net group  named  netGroup1
       between blockA/DATA_OUT*  and blockB/DATA_IN* with a budget distance 10
       microns  from internal connections inside the blockA to the start point
       of DATA_OUT* :

       modifyPipelineNetGroup netGroup1 -startTerm  blockA/DATA_OUT*  -endTerm
       blockB/DATA_IN* -startReserve 10

